body.name: Disney Baby Onlook 2-in-1 Convertible Car Seat, Rear-Facing 5-40 pounds and Forward-Facing 22-40 pounds and up to 43 inches, Mouseketeer Mickey
features: With two modes of use, this LATCH-equipped Cosco car seat accommodates infants from 5 pounds up to toddlers weighing 40 pounds in rear-facing mode and kids up to 40 pounds in forward-facing mode.
The five-point harness adjusts easily from the front of the seat and features six heights and three buckle locations.
In both the rear-facing and forward-facing modes, built-in side-impact protection keeps your little one extra secure.
Easily remove the machine-washable and dryer-safe car seat pad to clean.
Perfect for travel, the seat is certified for use on aircraft and gives your child a familiar seat during a flight.
body.description: Travel is more fun with Disney Baby along for the ride! all the way up to 40 pounds! Use the rear-facing position up to 40 pounds, forward-facing to 40 pounds, and for children as tall as 43, the Disney Baby Onlook 2-in-1 Convertible Car Seat keeps them safer during every stage with Side Impact Protection. This Disney Baby Car Seat also meets Federal and American Society for Testing and Materials Safety Standards.With kids in the car, messes happen. Now, thanks to the easy-to-clean car seat pad, theres no need to stress. The pad comes in a wide range of styles and colors, all of which remove from the seat and are both machine washable and dryer safe. A thorough wash is just a machine cycle away.If your chosen vehicle is an airplane, the Disney Baby Onlook 2-in-1 Convertible Car Seat has you covered. Certified for use on aircraft, it gives your child a familiar seat during the flight. The lightweight and compact design also get you through the airport without weighing you down. Two integrated cup holders make sure your copilot has plenty of room for drinks or a snack during the ride, whether on the ground or up in the air. The Disney Baby Onlook 2-in-1 Convertible Car Seat is proudly made by Cosco in Columbus, Indiana. Made by American families for American families.(Actual fit may vary. Not all children will comfortably fit in the sear for the full weight and height ranges listed.)

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Disney Baby Grow and Go 3-in-1 Convertible Car Seat Travel is more fun with Disney Baby along for the ride! all the way up to 40 pounds! Use the rear-facing position up to 40 pounds, forward-facing to 40 pounds, and for children as tall as 43, the Disney Baby Onlook 2-in-1 Convertible Car Seat keeps them safer during every stage with Side Impact Protection. The five-point harness adjusts easily from the front of the seat and features six heights and three buckle locations.In both the rear-facing and forward-facing modes, built-in side-impact protection keeps your little one extra secure.Easily remove the machine-washable and dryer-safe car seat pad to clean.Perfect for travel, the seat is certified for use on aircraft and gives your child a familiar seat during a flight.

3-In-1 Adaptability Rear-Facing Protection for Babies The Grow and Go can be used in the rear-facing position for newborns and growing toddlers, from 5 to 40 pounds. Forward-Facing for Toddlers and Kids In forward-facing mode, the Grow and Go keeps your child protected in a harness with side impact protection up to 65 pounds. Belt-Positioning Booster When your child is big enough, remove the harness to use the belt-positioning booster mode for kids up to 100 pounds.

Convenience for Everyday Life Messes Happen Kids sneak in snacks and you find them mushed into every crevice. The seat pad comes off without removing the harness, because let’s face it – you don’t have time for that. Handy Harness Holders It can be tough to get a child who’s arching their back in the car seat – because no one likes leaving the park. Harness holders make it easy to get “Archie” and “Floppy” into the seat. Reason to Raise Your Cup Kids always want to take one for the road. That’s why we’ve included two convenient cup holders, just in case they want to take two.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and reliable for travel.
reviews.reviewText: I used this as my travel car seat on a trip to Disney (obviously!). It had a simple 5 point harness that was a breeze to figure out. My child is big 1.5 year old and it fit perfectly. Installing in a car was easy too. It could have fit a smaller kid but I wouldn’t use with my own kid younger than 1.
